WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.918 --> 00:00:09.237
(epic theme playing)

2
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:17.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

3
00:01:21.225 --> 00:01:23.393
(vocalizing)

4
00:01:45.682 --> 00:01:47.718
(tense music playing)

5
00:01:47.751 --> 00:01:50.320
(water flowing)

6
00:01:50.354 --> 00:01:52.557
(indistinct yelling)

7
00:01:56.059 --> 00:01:58.395
(winces. groans)

8
00:02:02.366 --> 00:02:04.534
(people yelling)

9
00:02:07.237 --> 00:02:10.475
(distant screaming)

10
00:02:10.507 --> 00:02:13.410
King Viserys: Ser Ryam was a strong
Lord Commander

11
00:02:13.443 --> 00:02:15.245
of the Kingsguard.

12
00:02:16.214 --> 00:02:18.248
But he was ill for some time.

13
00:02:18.282 --> 00:02:19.883
He passed in peace. I hope.

14
00:02:19.916 --> 00:02:20.984
Grand Maester Mellos: Yes. Your Grace.

15
00:02:21.018 --> 00:02:22.352
He was found to have passed

16
00:02:22.386 --> 00:02:24.222
gently in his sleep.

17
00:02:24.254 --> 00:02:25.922
His remains are being prepared

18
00:02:25.957 --> 00:02:27.592
by the Silent Sisters.

19
00:02:27.624 --> 00:02:31.028
The succeeding Lord Commander.
Ser Harrold.

20
00:02:31.062 --> 00:02:32.597
would like to make
haste in finding

21
00:02:32.629 --> 00:02:35.399
Ser Ryam's replacement
on the Kingsguard.

22
00:02:35.432 --> 00:02:37.969
Ser Harrold Westerling: Your Grace. My lords.

23
00:02:38.368 --> 00:02:41.438
The Kingsguard must soon be restored
to its full complement of seven.

24
00:02:42.472 --> 00:02:43.807
With the help of the Hand.

25
00:02:43.840 --> 00:02:46.511
I've invited a number of
fine candidates to court.

26
00:02:46.543 --> 00:02:49.112
All have passed fair trials.

27
00:02:49.147 --> 00:02:50.314
(door opens)

28
00:02:52.683 --> 00:02:54.619
Four ships have now been lost.

29
00:02:54.651 --> 00:02:56.920
The last one was
flying my banner.

30
00:02:56.953 --> 00:02:58.990
The Stepstones have now
grown into a conflagration.

31
00:02:59.022 --> 00:03:01.425
yet you sit here
and dither about court business.

32
00:03:01.825 --> 00:03:03.827
Ser Otto Hightower: If you've something to discuss.
Lord Corlys...

33
00:03:03.860 --> 00:03:05.762
I want to know
what is to be done

34
00:03:05.796 --> 00:03:07.899
about my ships and my men.

35
00:03:07.931 --> 00:03:09.132
The Crown will compensate you

36
00:03:09.167 --> 00:03:11.301
for your ship and crew.
and make an offering

37
00:03:11.335 --> 00:03:15.305
- to the men's families.
- I don't want compensation.

38
00:03:16.606 --> 00:03:19.076
I want to seize
the Stepstones by force

39
00:03:19.110 --> 00:03:20.510
and burn out this Crabfeeder.

40
00:03:20.545 --> 00:03:23.580
I am not prepared to start
a war with the Free Cities.

41
00:03:23.613 --> 00:03:26.284
These pirates are
not the Free Cities.

42
00:03:26.316 --> 00:03:29.953
Who do you think provides them
with their ships and tender?

43
00:03:29.986 --> 00:03:31.855
In all of its history. my lord.

44
00:03:31.888 --> 00:03:33.857
the Seven Kingdoms
have never entered

45
00:03:33.890 --> 00:03:35.726
open war with the Free Cities.

46
00:03:35.760 --> 00:03:37.395
Were that to happen.

47
00:03:37.427 --> 00:03:40.497
the losses would
be incalculable.

48
00:03:44.101 --> 00:03:47.437
What reason does
the Crabfeeder have to fear us?

49
00:03:49.674 --> 00:03:52.242
The King's own brother has been allowed
to seize Dragonstone

50
00:03:52.275 --> 00:03:55.313
and fortify it with an army
of his gold cloaks.

51
00:03:55.345 --> 00:03:58.014
Daemon has squatted there
for over half a year

52
00:03:58.049 --> 00:04:00.117
without even a protest
from The Crown.

53
00:04:00.151 --> 00:04:02.886
I'll caution you. Lord Corlys.

54
00:04:02.919 --> 00:04:06.857
a seat at the King's table
does not make you his equal.

55
00:04:10.061 --> 00:04:12.697
I have acted. Corlys.

56
00:04:12.729 --> 00:04:15.800
I've sent envoys
to Pentos and Volantis

57
00:04:15.832 --> 00:04:18.502
to see if we might
find common cause.

58
00:04:18.535 --> 00:04:21.671
Ships and men are at the ready.

59
00:04:21.706 --> 00:04:25.776
The Stepstones
will be settled... in time.

60
00:04:25.810 --> 00:04:28.378
You have dragonriders. father.

61
00:04:34.619 --> 00:04:35.919
Send us.

62
00:04:38.021 --> 00:04:39.190
(soft chuckle)

63
00:04:40.490 --> 00:04:43.828
It isn't that simple.
Rhaenyra.

64
00:04:43.860 --> 00:04:45.962
It would be a show of force.

65
00:04:45.997 --> 00:04:48.398
At least the Princess
has a plan.

66
00:04:52.035 --> 00:04:54.304
- I only meant that we should at least...
- Otto: Perhaps. uh...

67
00:04:54.704 --> 00:04:58.942
there's some better use
for the Princess's talents. Your Grace.

68
00:05:01.578 --> 00:05:03.613
King Viserys: Why don't you take
the Princess to see about the new

69
00:05:03.648 --> 00:05:05.615
Kingsguard posting.
Lord Commander?

70
00:05:07.218 --> 00:05:09.052
A fine idea. Your Grace.

71
00:05:10.687 --> 00:05:13.423
This knight will
protect you as well.

72
00:05:13.457 --> 00:05:15.258
You should choose.

73
00:05:18.296 --> 00:05:19.429
(scoffs)

74
00:05:24.634 --> 00:05:26.237
(door opens)

75
00:05:33.276 --> 00:05:35.545
(birds chirping)

76
00:05:35.579 --> 00:05:37.714
Harrold: Ser Desmond Caron.

77
00:05:37.747 --> 00:05:40.083
a fine knight. Princess.

78
00:05:40.116 --> 00:05:42.320
Step forward. Ser Desmond.

79
00:05:44.454 --> 00:05:45.989
Son of Ser Royce Caron.

80
00:05:46.022 --> 00:05:48.625
Ser Desmond has proved
strong and steady

81
00:05:48.658 --> 00:05:51.495
in both the tourney lists
and without.

82
00:05:51.928 --> 00:05:54.532
While traveling through the Kingswood
on his way to King's Landing.

83
00:05:54.564 --> 00:05:57.734
Ser Desmond recently brought
a would-be poacher

84
00:05:57.767 --> 00:05:59.135
to justice.

85
00:06:09.513 --> 00:06:13.016
You might thank him
for his leal service. Princess.

86
00:06:13.049 --> 00:06:16.620
We thank you for your loyal
service to The Crown. ser.

87
00:06:17.854 --> 00:06:19.689
(footsteps departing)

88
00:06:27.964 --> 00:06:30.201
Harrold: Ser Rymun Mallister.

89
00:06:32.235 --> 00:06:35.238
Son of Lord Lymond Mallister
of Seagard.

90
00:06:35.272 --> 00:06:37.707
Winner of the melee
at Cider Hall.

91
00:06:37.742 --> 00:06:40.644
He was the last mounted
of three-and-twenty knights.

92
00:06:40.677 --> 00:06:42.747
Ser Rymun was knighted
at eight-and-ten.

93
00:06:42.779 --> 00:06:45.282
Do any of these knights
have combat experience?

94
00:06:46.416 --> 00:06:48.285
Beyond capturing poachers.

95
00:06:48.319 --> 00:06:50.520
(city bells tolling)

96
00:06:56.327 --> 00:06:58.562
Harrold: Ser Criston Cole.

97
00:07:04.235 --> 00:07:07.537
Son of the steward
of the Lord of Blackhaven.

98
00:07:09.472 --> 00:07:11.509
Be welcome. Ser Criston.

99
00:07:13.476 --> 00:07:15.845
You saw combat
in the Stormlands.

100
00:07:15.880 --> 00:07:17.882
Dornish marches. Princess.

101
00:07:18.315 --> 00:07:22.253
I fought for a year as a foot solider
against the Dornish incursions.

102
00:07:22.285 --> 00:07:24.321
Ser Arlan Dondarrion
knighted me after we razed

103
00:07:24.355 --> 00:07:26.656
two of the watchtowers
along the Boneway.

104
00:07:32.062 --> 00:07:34.197
I choose Ser Criston Cole.

105
00:07:34.230 --> 00:07:38.369
Let's not be too hasty.
Princess.

106
00:07:38.401 --> 00:07:41.571
There's no doubt Ser Criston
is a fine warrior.

107
00:07:41.605 --> 00:07:44.140
but houses such as
Crakehall and Mallister

108
00:07:44.175 --> 00:07:46.876
are important allies
of The Crown.

109
00:07:46.911 --> 00:07:48.078
Seagard. for instance.

110
00:07:48.111 --> 00:07:49.613
is the realm's prime defense

111
00:07:49.647 --> 00:07:51.382
against reavers
from the Iron Islands.

112
00:07:51.414 --> 00:07:53.416
Those men are tourney knights.

113
00:07:53.783 --> 00:07:56.252
My father should be defended by a man
who's known real combat.

114
00:07:58.755 --> 00:08:00.123
Should he not?

115
00:08:02.158 --> 00:08:03.893
Of course. Princess.

116
00:08:03.928 --> 00:08:06.896
Well. let us plan Ser Criston's
investiture then.

117
00:08:10.233 --> 00:08:12.837
(city bells tolling)

118
00:08:15.271 --> 00:08:18.074
King Viserys: The Valyrian capital
was built into a volcano.

119
00:08:18.108 --> 00:08:20.510
much like Dragonstone.

120
00:08:20.543 --> 00:08:23.681
And the dragonlords.
the highest of the nobility.

121
00:08:23.713 --> 00:08:26.616
lived here.
at the volcanic face.

122
00:08:26.650 --> 00:08:30.020
closest to the source
of their magic and power.

123
00:08:30.054 --> 00:08:32.122
And this was the Anogrion.

124
00:08:33.923 --> 00:08:36.427
Where the bloodmages
worked their craft.

125
00:08:38.728 --> 00:08:41.164
It is truly wondrous
what you've built.

126
00:08:41.197 --> 00:08:42.333
Oh no.

127
00:08:43.400 --> 00:08:45.069
I only pore over the histories

128
00:08:45.101 --> 00:08:46.936
and provide the plans.

129
00:08:46.971 --> 00:08:49.806
The stonemasons
built the structures.

130
00:08:49.839 --> 00:08:51.007
Do you believe that Westeros

131
00:08:51.041 --> 00:08:52.809
can be another Valyria.
Your Grace?

132
00:08:52.842 --> 00:08:53.885
That depends.

133
00:08:53.992 --> 00:08:55.035
whether you speak
of the Freehold

134
00:08:55.045 --> 00:08:57.280
at its height or at its fall.

135
00:08:58.481 --> 00:09:00.084
Over a thousand dragons.

136
00:09:00.116 --> 00:09:03.454
a navy large enough to span
the seas of the world.

137
00:09:06.289 --> 00:09:10.126
The glory of Old Valyria
will never be seen again.

138
00:09:10.160 --> 00:09:12.429
(object breaks)
Seven Hells.

139
00:09:16.332 --> 00:09:18.501
(birds cawing)

140
00:09:28.012 --> 00:09:30.381
Tell me. how is Rhaenyra?

141
00:09:30.413 --> 00:09:32.116
- What do you mean?
- Well. these days.

142
00:09:32.148 --> 00:09:34.851
she doesn't say more
than a few words to me.

143
00:09:34.884 --> 00:09:37.454
I think she might
find it difficult...

144
00:09:38.489 --> 00:09:40.724
to discuss personal matters.

145
00:09:42.225 --> 00:09:43.693
It will take time.

146
00:09:45.563 --> 00:09:47.731
It did when I lost
mine own mother.

147
00:09:53.803 --> 00:09:56.040
I wish she would approach me.

148
00:09:57.408 --> 00:09:59.542
What if you went to her?

149
00:09:59.577 --> 00:10:01.512
There are times when
I would rather face

150
00:10:01.544 --> 00:10:02.780
the Black Dread himself

151
00:10:02.812 --> 00:10:04.782
than mine own daughter of 15.

152
00:10:04.814 --> 00:10:06.050
(chuckles)

153
00:10:07.650 --> 00:10:11.554
I think she would open
herself to you if invited.

154
00:10:11.589 --> 00:10:15.358
You do have such an easy way about you.
Your Grace.

155
00:10:16.726 --> 00:10:19.063
Um...

156
00:10:19.095 --> 00:10:22.499
you do not mention our talks to Rhaenyra.
do you?

157
00:10:24.734 --> 00:10:26.070
I just...

158
00:10:27.137 --> 00:10:30.074
I fear that she wouldn't
understand them.

159
00:10:30.106 --> 00:10:31.908
No. Your Grace.

160
00:10:38.549 --> 00:10:40.750
(seabirds cawing)

161
00:10:45.089 --> 00:10:47.857
It's only been half a year
since my mother died.

162
00:10:47.891 --> 00:10:50.059
and already they tried
to marry my father off

163
00:10:50.094 --> 00:10:52.262
and replace me as heir.

164
00:10:52.295 --> 00:10:54.297
I know those men
and how they plot

165
00:10:54.330 --> 00:10:57.568
in their secret councils
when I've been sent away.

166
00:10:57.600 --> 00:11:01.604
You cannot worry at the matters
of lords and kings. Rhaenyra.

167
00:11:03.339 --> 00:11:05.608
What if your father
were to remarry?

168
00:11:14.050 --> 00:11:16.252
Your father loves you.

169
00:11:22.126 --> 00:11:25.161
He chose you for his heir.

170
00:11:25.195 --> 00:11:28.097
He didn't choose me.
He spurns Daemon.

171
00:11:45.481 --> 00:11:47.283
Kneel with me.

172
00:12:04.033 --> 00:12:06.970
I find this is a way
to be with my mother.

173
00:12:08.439 --> 00:12:10.673
Here in the quiet
of the Sept...

174
00:12:11.875 --> 00:12:13.676
I feel close to her.

175
00:12:18.615 --> 00:12:22.619
- I know it sounds foolish.
- I don't think it's foolish.

176
00:12:23.554 --> 00:12:25.788
- I don't.
- Good...

177
00:12:28.958 --> 00:12:31.195
because I thought you might try.

178
00:12:32.930 --> 00:12:34.230
I...

179
00:12:34.264 --> 00:12:38.067
If not for me. then.
perhaps for them.

180
00:12:39.002 --> 00:12:40.370
(sighs)

181
00:13:03.393 --> 00:13:06.095
What do I say?

182
00:13:06.130 --> 00:13:07.931
Whatever you wish.

183
00:13:09.065 --> 00:13:11.367
It's only for you
and the gods to know.

184
00:13:19.575 --> 00:13:22.412
(poignant music playing)

185
00:13:35.291 --> 00:13:37.393
(crying)

186
00:13:45.835 --> 00:13:49.540
I want him to see me as
more than his little girl.

187
00:13:51.975 --> 00:13:55.311
Mine own father does not know
the language of girls either.

188
00:13:55.345 --> 00:13:57.548
(Rhaenyra chuckles)

189
00:13:59.248 --> 00:14:02.051
When I wish to talk with him...

190
00:14:02.085 --> 00:14:04.587
I know that I must
make the effort.

191
00:14:08.224 --> 00:14:09.393
Thank you.

192
00:14:21.405 --> 00:14:23.307
Corlys Velaryon: Your Grace.

193
00:14:23.339 --> 00:14:25.441
King Viserys: I'm glad we could meet.

194
00:14:25.475 --> 00:14:27.010
I know tempers ran hot today.

195
00:14:27.044 --> 00:14:29.345
and I wanted to assure you
how much I value the bond

196
00:14:29.379 --> 00:14:31.347
between our houses.

197
00:14:31.381 --> 00:14:34.283
Rhaenys is my favorite
cousin after all.

198
00:14:35.451 --> 00:14:38.454
I wish to apologize
for the tenor

199
00:14:38.488 --> 00:14:40.858
at the Small Council today.
Your Grace.

200
00:14:40.890 --> 00:14:42.925
It was not my intent
to make offense.

201
00:14:43.794 --> 00:14:45.194
Your fleet is one of the realm's

202
00:14:45.229 --> 00:14:48.065
most important assets.
Lord Corlys.

203
00:14:48.097 --> 00:14:49.600
But you must understand.

204
00:14:49.632 --> 00:14:52.101
as King. it is my
obligation to avoid war

205
00:14:52.135 --> 00:14:54.438
until such time
it is unavoidable.

206
00:14:54.470 --> 00:14:56.939
None among us desire open war.

207
00:14:58.274 --> 00:15:01.844
Might I speak plainly.
Your Grace?

208
00:15:01.879 --> 00:15:05.381
I always welcome the unfettered thoughts
of my council.

209
00:15:05.415 --> 00:15:07.150
I fear that the eyes
of our enemies

210
00:15:07.183 --> 00:15:10.653
are presently fixed
on the Red Keep.

211
00:15:10.686 --> 00:15:12.155
The Queen has passed.

212
00:15:12.188 --> 00:15:14.390
A girl has been named
heir to the Iron Throne.

213
00:15:14.424 --> 00:15:16.292
the first in its history.

214
00:15:16.325 --> 00:15:17.895
The King's brother.
so disinherited.

215
00:15:17.927 --> 00:15:20.229
has claimed the Targaryen seat
on Dragonstone

216
00:15:20.264 --> 00:15:22.698
without challenge.

217
00:15:22.733 --> 00:15:25.401
And now. a foreign power
has established a colony

218
00:15:25.435 --> 00:15:28.771
in our most critical
shipping lane.

219
00:15:28.805 --> 00:15:32.476
You paint such an aspirant portrait
of my reign. Lord Corlys.

220
00:15:32.508 --> 00:15:35.411
It is an honest one. cousin.

221
00:15:35.812 --> 00:15:39.515
At the moment. The Crown is perceived
as being vulnerable.

222
00:15:39.549 --> 00:15:41.485
And a blind incursion
in the Stepstones

223
00:15:41.517 --> 00:15:43.921
is the only way to demonstrate
that we are not?

224
00:15:43.953 --> 00:15:45.321
Corlys: To elude a storm.

225
00:15:45.354 --> 00:15:47.590
you can either sail into it

226
00:15:47.623 --> 00:15:49.158
or around it.

227
00:15:49.192 --> 00:15:53.030
But you must never
await its coming.

228
00:15:53.062 --> 00:15:56.099
Do you have a specific
course of action to propose.

229
00:15:56.133 --> 00:15:57.935
my lord?

230
00:16:00.137 --> 00:16:02.738
Join our families.

231
00:16:02.773 --> 00:16:04.340
Wed our daughter. Laena.

232
00:16:04.373 --> 00:16:07.743
Unite the two great surviving
Valyrian houses.

233
00:16:07.778 --> 00:16:08.820
With the Targaryen dragons

234
00:16:09.112 --> 00:16:11.048
and the Velaryon fleet
bound in blood.

235
00:16:11.080 --> 00:16:12.516
you can show the realm

236
00:16:12.548 --> 00:16:15.485
that The Crown's strongest days
are ahead...

237
00:16:15.519 --> 00:16:16.687
not behind.

238
00:16:16.719 --> 00:16:18.921
(tense music playing)

239
00:16:21.557 --> 00:16:23.659
I must admit...

240
00:16:23.694 --> 00:16:26.295
I haven't given
marriage much thought.

241
00:16:26.330 --> 00:16:28.731
It hasn't even been half a year
since Aemma passed.

242
00:16:28.764 --> 00:16:30.901
The realm expects you
to take a new wife

243
00:16:30.933 --> 00:16:32.336
soon or late. Your Grace.

244
00:16:32.368 --> 00:16:35.539
to strengthen your line
and produce more heirs.

245
00:16:35.571 --> 00:16:39.108
You could not ask for
a stronger match than Laena.

246
00:16:58.294 --> 00:17:00.496
(crickets chirping)

247
00:17:06.869 --> 00:17:09.305
We haven't spoken much...

248
00:17:11.842 --> 00:17:13.276
since.

249
00:17:16.512 --> 00:17:18.414
A regret of mine.

250
00:17:19.682 --> 00:17:23.387
We should be free to speak our minds
to one another.

251
00:17:23.419 --> 00:17:25.087
You can say whatever
you'd like.

252
00:17:25.122 --> 00:17:27.124
You are the King.

253
00:17:27.723 --> 00:17:28.859
(chuckles)

254
00:17:34.997 --> 00:17:39.335
I loved your mother...
very much.

255
00:17:42.438 --> 00:17:43.974
As did I.

256
00:17:50.580 --> 00:17:52.616
(tapping on table)

257
00:17:54.684 --> 00:17:56.018
(sighs)

258
00:17:59.822 --> 00:18:03.292
Ser Harrold provided a fine
field of tourney knights.

259
00:18:03.326 --> 00:18:04.660
Oh?

260
00:18:05.695 --> 00:18:07.196
But in questioning them.

261
00:18:07.563 --> 00:18:10.000
I discovered that Ser Criston
was the only man among them

262
00:18:10.032 --> 00:18:12.969
with true battle experience.
(chuckles)

263
00:18:13.003 --> 00:18:15.906
He'll make a fine
knight of the Kingsguard.

264
00:18:21.043 --> 00:18:24.548
- Today at Small Council...
- Pay it no mind.

265
00:18:24.981 --> 00:18:27.883
- I. I thought I might have had some insight. but...
- You're young.

266
00:18:28.751 --> 00:18:30.152
You will learn.

267
00:18:54.845 --> 00:18:58.514
Mellos: This is our best chance
to save the digit. Your Grace.

268
00:19:00.249 --> 00:19:02.385
The maggots will
remove the dead flesh

269
00:19:02.418 --> 00:19:05.354
and hopefully stop
the advance of the rot.

270
00:19:10.861 --> 00:19:13.597
I held an audience
earlier today

271
00:19:13.629 --> 00:19:15.866
with Lord Corlys
and Princess Rhaenys.

272
00:19:15.898 --> 00:19:18.068
That was most charitable
of you. Your Grace.

273
00:19:18.100 --> 00:19:21.570
I'm sure Lord Corlys
appreciated the spirit of it.

274
00:19:21.605 --> 00:19:23.806
He proposed a marriage.

275
00:19:24.940 --> 00:19:27.943
To whom. Your Grace?

276
00:19:27.978 --> 00:19:30.212
The Lady Laena.

277
00:19:30.247 --> 00:19:32.315
To combine the strength
of our houses.

278
00:19:32.349 --> 00:19:35.851
and demonstrate my reign's
strongest days are ahead.

279
00:19:35.866 --> 00:19:36.908
not behind.

280
00:19:36.919 --> 00:19:40.022
Lord Corlys has
overreached. Your Grace.

281
00:19:40.056 --> 00:19:43.659
Such matters must be discussed
with the Small Council.

282
00:19:43.693 --> 00:19:46.762
That is what I'm doing.
presently.

283
00:19:47.930 --> 00:19:51.834
So... what is your
advice. dear Otto.

284
00:19:52.668 --> 00:19:55.137
Otto: The Lady Laena...

285
00:19:55.172 --> 00:19:57.707
is young. Your Grace.

286
00:19:57.741 --> 00:20:01.111
Indeed. but the wounds
made by the Great Council

287
00:20:01.143 --> 00:20:02.945
still linger. my King.

288
00:20:02.978 --> 00:20:06.482
A match with their daughter
would go a long way towards

289
00:20:06.515 --> 00:20:08.451
sealing the breach

290
00:20:08.484 --> 00:20:11.388
and uniting the two
great Valyrian houses

291
00:20:11.420 --> 00:20:15.091
would certainly signal unity
throughout the realm

292
00:20:15.125 --> 00:20:17.194
and beyond.

293
00:20:17.226 --> 00:20:19.995
The Grand Maester's
reasoning is sound.

294
00:20:21.497 --> 00:20:23.332
I do fear what
Rhaenyra might think.

295
00:20:23.366 --> 00:20:25.434
Mellos: What does it matter.
Your Grace?

296
00:20:25.468 --> 00:20:27.737
Her mother has passed.

297
00:20:27.771 --> 00:20:30.539
Her father must propagate
the royal line.

298
00:20:37.279 --> 00:20:42.284
I. uh. dearly loved
my own lady wife.

299
00:20:42.319 --> 00:20:45.621
The pain of her passing
still haunts me.

300
00:20:47.089 --> 00:20:49.326
And to be compelled to...

301
00:20:50.259 --> 00:20:53.129
replace her for duty's sake.

302
00:20:54.598 --> 00:20:56.399
You are the King.

303
00:20:57.234 --> 00:20:59.468
But I do not envy you.

304
00:21:04.441 --> 00:21:06.642
(birds chirping)

305
00:21:11.448 --> 00:21:13.649
(insects buzzing)

306
00:21:27.998 --> 00:21:30.966
What was it like
flying the Black Dread?

307
00:21:31.001 --> 00:21:34.036
You were Balerion's
last rider.

308
00:21:34.069 --> 00:21:37.406
Only for a short time
before he died.

309
00:21:37.440 --> 00:21:38.483
With Balerion

310
00:21:38.742 --> 00:21:42.077
died the last memory
of Valyria of Old.

311
00:21:42.112 --> 00:21:44.413
But Vhagar still lives...

312
00:21:44.447 --> 00:21:46.081
somewhere.
(King Viserys sighs)

313
00:21:46.116 --> 00:21:48.617
Bit too large
for the Dragonpit.

314
00:21:48.652 --> 00:21:52.087
Some would say too
large for our world.

315
00:21:52.122 --> 00:21:55.324
- Do you know where she nests?
- I'm sorry?

316
00:21:55.357 --> 00:21:57.359
Do you know where Vhagar is now?

317
00:21:57.394 --> 00:22:00.162
Um. the Dragonkeepers
believe she made home

318
00:22:00.196 --> 00:22:02.598
somewhere on the coast
of the Narrow Sea.

319
00:22:02.631 --> 00:22:06.303
The workers at Spicetown report
hearing her song at times.

320
00:22:06.335 --> 00:22:10.407
They say it is a sad thing.
(King Viserys sighs)

321
00:22:10.439 --> 00:22:12.741
I imagine even
dragons get lonely.

322
00:22:17.112 --> 00:22:18.714
Your Grace...

323
00:22:19.548 --> 00:22:21.484
it would be a great honor

324
00:22:21.518 --> 00:22:25.821
to join our houses
as they were in Old Valyria.

325
00:22:25.855 --> 00:22:27.189
I would give you many children

326
00:22:27.223 --> 00:22:29.024
of pure Valyrian blood

327
00:22:29.059 --> 00:22:31.428
so that we might strengthen
the royal line

328
00:22:31.460 --> 00:22:32.896
and the realm.

329
00:22:32.928 --> 00:22:35.564
Is that what your father
told you to say?

330
00:22:40.236 --> 00:22:42.104
What did your mother tell you?

331
00:22:43.572 --> 00:22:47.109
That I wouldn't have to bed you
until I turned 14.

332
00:22:51.181 --> 00:22:52.515
(sighs)

333
00:22:53.249 --> 00:22:55.452
(pensive music playing)

334
00:23:14.403 --> 00:23:16.639
It bothers you. does it not?

335
00:23:21.644 --> 00:23:23.812
My father is a king.

336
00:23:23.847 --> 00:23:25.915
It is his duty
to take a new wife

337
00:23:25.949 --> 00:23:27.117
and strengthen his line.

338
00:23:27.149 --> 00:23:28.417
I did not ask for
a lesson in politics.

339
00:23:28.450 --> 00:23:29.885
I asked whether
this bothers you.

340
00:23:29.919 --> 00:23:31.388
Laena is your daughter.
Princess.

341
00:23:31.420 --> 00:23:33.455
Does it bother you?

342
00:23:34.356 --> 00:23:35.791
Of course. it does.

343
00:23:37.459 --> 00:23:40.964
But I understand
the order of things.

344
00:23:42.364 --> 00:23:45.067
I'm not sure you do.

345
00:23:47.303 --> 00:23:50.639
If you mean to elicit
some anger from me.

346
00:23:50.673 --> 00:23:54.443
you should know that
you're failing. Princess.

347
00:23:54.476 --> 00:23:56.312
Quite the opposite.

348
00:23:59.349 --> 00:24:01.050
Whether it's to my daughter
or to someone else's.

349
00:24:01.083 --> 00:24:04.820
your father will remarry
sooner than late.

350
00:24:04.853 --> 00:24:07.389
His new wife will
produce new heirs.

351
00:24:07.756 --> 00:24:10.360
and chances are better than not
that one of those will be male.

352
00:24:10.392 --> 00:24:13.062
And when that boy comes of age
and your father has passed.

353
00:24:13.095 --> 00:24:16.231
the men of the realm
will expect him to be heir.

354
00:24:16.266 --> 00:24:17.901
not you.

355
00:24:20.035 --> 00:24:22.338
Because that is
the order of things.

356
00:24:24.340 --> 00:24:26.842
When I'm Queen.
I will create a new order.

357
00:24:26.875 --> 00:24:28.210
(Princess Rhaenys chuckles)

358
00:24:28.243 --> 00:24:31.014
How I wish that could be.
Rhaenyra.

359
00:24:31.046 --> 00:24:33.650
But the men of the realm
already had their opportunity

360
00:24:33.682 --> 00:24:36.186
to appoint a ruling queen
at the Great Council

361
00:24:36.218 --> 00:24:38.021
and they denied it.

362
00:24:38.053 --> 00:24:41.624
They denied you.
Princess Rhaenys.

363
00:24:41.658 --> 00:24:44.326
"The Queen Who Never Was."

364
00:24:44.360 --> 00:24:45.594
But they bent the knee to me

365
00:24:45.628 --> 00:24:47.162
and called me
heir to the throne.

366
00:24:47.197 --> 00:24:48.597
Do you remind your
father's men of that

367
00:24:48.631 --> 00:24:50.599
as you carry their cups?

368
00:24:54.770 --> 00:24:56.673
Here is the hard truth.

369
00:24:56.705 --> 00:25:00.743
which no one else has
the heart to tell you.

370
00:25:00.776 --> 00:25:04.513
Men would sooner put
the realm to the torch

371
00:25:04.546 --> 00:25:07.816
than see a woman
ascend the Iron Throne.

372
00:25:10.053 --> 00:25:12.388
(tense music playing)

373
00:25:12.422 --> 00:25:15.290
And your father is no fool.

374
00:25:29.004 --> 00:25:32.808
King Viserys: The Small Council is
urging me to remarry.

375
00:25:34.176 --> 00:25:37.112
It seems the realm
wants for a new queen.

376
00:25:42.184 --> 00:25:45.821
A good and kind queen
will give comfort to your subjects.

377
00:25:50.793 --> 00:25:54.464
- Does the Small Council have a particular lady in mind?
- Uh...

378
00:25:55.931 --> 00:26:00.836
Lord Corlys Velaryon has offered
the hand of his daughter.

379
00:26:00.869 --> 00:26:03.439
the Lady Laena.

380
00:26:03.473 --> 00:26:05.708
A very strong match. Your Grace.

381
00:26:06.975 --> 00:26:11.413
I must admit. I.
I don't know Laena very well.

382
00:26:11.447 --> 00:26:13.716
I'm sure that she
is good and kind.

383
00:26:14.117 --> 00:26:17.786
and that she will enjoy your company.
as I have. Your Grace.

384
00:26:33.036 --> 00:26:34.870
I brought you something.

385
00:26:55.158 --> 00:26:57.493
I asked the stonemasons
to mend it.

386
00:26:57.527 --> 00:26:58.894
(chuckles)

387
00:27:01.331 --> 00:27:03.265
This is. um.

388
00:27:03.298 --> 00:27:06.401
a very kind gesture. Alicent.

389
00:27:10.506 --> 00:27:12.775
Very kind.
(knocking on door)

390
00:27:19.616 --> 00:27:21.850
Come.
(door opens)

391
00:27:23.886 --> 00:27:26.356
Harrold: The Hand. Your Grace.

392
00:27:28.157 --> 00:27:30.360
(door closes)

393
00:27:30.392 --> 00:27:32.327
Your Grace. I've called
the Small Council

394
00:27:32.362 --> 00:27:33.962
to an emergency session.

395
00:27:33.997 --> 00:27:35.130
Why?

396
00:27:36.199 --> 00:27:38.901
I think it best
you hear it directly.

397
00:27:40.068 --> 00:27:41.436
Very well.

398
00:27:48.076 --> 00:27:49.878
(door opens)

399
00:27:51.180 --> 00:27:52.781
(door closes)

400
00:27:52.815 --> 00:27:55.050
{\an8}(speaking High Valyrian)

401
00:28:12.100 --> 00:28:15.038
- Daemon.
- The Prince left a missive.

402
00:28:15.070 --> 00:28:18.106
which I believe might explain.

403
00:28:18.141 --> 00:28:20.976
"It is the pleasure
of Daemon Targaryen.

404
00:28:21.009 --> 00:28:22.779
"the Prince of Dragonstone

405
00:28:22.811 --> 00:28:26.783
"and rightful heir
to the Iron Throne.

406
00:28:26.815 --> 00:28:29.651
"to announce that he is
to take a second wife

407
00:28:29.686 --> 00:28:32.554
"in the tradition
of Old Valyria.

408
00:28:32.588 --> 00:28:37.894
"She is to assume the title
Lady Mysaria of Dragonstone.

409
00:28:37.926 --> 00:28:39.761
"Her Grace is with child

410
00:28:39.796 --> 00:28:45.100
"and is to have a dragon's egg
placed in the babe's cradle

411
00:28:45.133 --> 00:28:48.438
in the custom
of House Targaryen."

412
00:28:48.470 --> 00:28:53.041
The Prince has invited you
to his wedding. Your Grace.

413
00:28:53.076 --> 00:28:56.478
- It is in two days' time.
- Gods be good.

414
00:28:56.511 --> 00:28:58.580
Who is Lady Mysaria?

415
00:28:58.614 --> 00:29:02.652
- Mellos: We believe...
- Otto: Daemon's whore.

416
00:29:02.684 --> 00:29:06.054
- This is nothing less than sedition.
- I strongly agree. sire.

417
00:29:06.089 --> 00:29:08.925
My brother wishes to provoke me.

418
00:29:08.957 --> 00:29:10.959
To answer is to give
him what he wants.

419
00:29:10.993 --> 00:29:13.328
The realm is watching.
Your Grace.

420
00:29:13.362 --> 00:29:15.030
King Viserys: What would you have me do?

421
00:29:15.063 --> 00:29:17.499
Send him to the Wall?

422
00:29:17.532 --> 00:29:19.601
Perhaps I could put
his head on a spike.

423
00:29:19.635 --> 00:29:21.503
Otto: Daemon has seized Dragonstone.

424
00:29:21.536 --> 00:29:24.373
has surrounded himself
with an army of gold cloaks.

425
00:29:24.406 --> 00:29:26.708
and has now stolen
a dangerous weapon...

426
00:29:26.743 --> 00:29:29.011
(speaking High Valyrian)

427
00:29:54.504 --> 00:29:57.673
Assemble a detachment. Otto.

428
00:29:57.707 --> 00:29:59.675
I will go to Dragonstone
and drag Daemon back

429
00:29:59.709 --> 00:30:03.211
- to face justice myself.
- Otto: Your Grace.

430
00:30:03.246 --> 00:30:05.647
My apologies. Your Grace.
but I cannot allow it.

431
00:30:05.681 --> 00:30:07.316
It's too dangerous.

432
00:30:07.350 --> 00:30:10.253
Daemon is without limit.

433
00:30:10.285 --> 00:30:12.554
Let me go to Dragonstone.

434
00:30:30.072 --> 00:30:32.275
(pensive music playing)

435
00:30:37.412 --> 00:30:39.214
(Otto sighs)

436
00:30:39.247 --> 00:30:42.617
You're the most
comely girl at court.

437
00:30:42.652 --> 00:30:45.087
Why do you destroy yourself?

438
00:30:46.121 --> 00:30:47.255
Hm?

439
00:30:51.194 --> 00:30:53.628
Will you see the King tonight?

440
00:30:56.331 --> 00:30:57.934
If you wish it.

441
00:31:00.969 --> 00:31:03.872
- Good day. Ser Criston.
- My Lady.

442
00:31:03.905 --> 00:31:07.075
I've assembled 20 of your best
household guards. my Lord Hand.

443
00:31:07.109 --> 00:31:09.811
Sir Harrold will also join us.

444
00:31:09.846 --> 00:31:12.080
(tense music playing)

445
00:31:13.416 --> 00:31:16.786
Alicent: Please look after
the Hand. Ser Criston.

446
00:31:55.992 --> 00:31:58.160
(waves crashing)

447
00:32:21.017 --> 00:32:22.852
(footsteps approaching)

448
00:32:36.531 --> 00:32:39.000
Welcome to Dragonstone. Otto.

449
00:32:41.037 --> 00:32:45.207
Otto: Your occupation of this
island is at an end.

450
00:32:45.240 --> 00:32:47.410
You're to relinquish
the dragon's egg.

451
00:32:47.442 --> 00:32:48.945
disband your army.

452
00:32:48.977 --> 00:32:51.847
banish your whore...

453
00:32:51.881 --> 00:32:54.483
and leave Dragonstone
by order of His Grace.

454
00:32:54.517 --> 00:32:56.918
- King Viserys...
- Where is the King? I don't see him.

455
00:32:57.352 --> 00:33:01.256
His Grace would never lower himself
to entertain such a mummer's farce.

456
00:33:06.394 --> 00:33:07.996
Ser Crispin. wasn't it?

457
00:33:08.029 --> 00:33:09.664
Ser Criston Cole: Ser Criston Cole. my Prince.

458
00:33:09.699 --> 00:33:12.134
Ah. yes. apologies.
I couldn't recall.

459
00:33:12.535 --> 00:33:15.203
Perhaps my Prince recalls when
I knocked him off his horse.

460
00:33:16.037 --> 00:33:18.039
(chuckles) Very good.

461
00:33:18.074 --> 00:33:21.077
Otto: This is a truly
pathetic show. Daemon.

462
00:33:21.109 --> 00:33:23.011
Are you so desperate
for the King's attention

463
00:33:23.044 --> 00:33:24.779
that you've resorted
to skulking about

464
00:33:24.814 --> 00:33:26.916
- like a common cutpurse?
- I'm simply keeping

465
00:33:26.948 --> 00:33:28.283
with the traditions of my house.

466
00:33:28.316 --> 00:33:30.118
the same as my brother
did for his heir.

467
00:33:30.485 --> 00:33:33.155
Those traditions are for the trueborn
children of royalty.

468
00:33:33.189 --> 00:33:36.658
not for bastards fathered
on a common whore.

469
00:33:36.691 --> 00:33:38.693
Lady Mysaria is to be my wife.

470
00:33:38.728 --> 00:33:40.096
Otto: This is an abomination.

471
00:33:40.128 --> 00:33:42.030
With every breath
you soil your name.

472
00:33:42.063 --> 00:33:43.865
your house.
and your brother's reign.

473
00:33:43.899 --> 00:33:48.403
Our love does not know
titles and traditions.

474
00:33:48.436 --> 00:33:50.805
And what of you.
men of the City Watch?

475
00:33:50.840 --> 00:33:52.340
Aiding the Prince
in his treason?

476
00:33:52.375 --> 00:33:54.477
Prince Daemon: The King made me
their commander.

477
00:33:54.509 --> 00:33:56.144
They are loyal to me.

478
00:33:56.946 --> 00:33:59.147
You've come for the egg.

479
00:34:00.415 --> 00:34:01.917
Here it is.

480
00:34:03.151 --> 00:34:04.854
Are you mad?

481
00:34:05.253 --> 00:34:08.858
- You'd never survive this.
- Well. happily. neither would you.

482
00:34:09.257 --> 00:34:14.062
To choose violence. here.
is to declare war against your King.

483
00:34:14.095 --> 00:34:15.463
Wonderful.

484
00:34:16.531 --> 00:34:17.799
Even if it ends in the death

485
00:34:17.832 --> 00:34:20.136
of your unborn child
and its mother?

486
00:34:27.777 --> 00:34:29.377
(rumbling)

487
00:34:29.412 --> 00:34:31.614
(Caraxes screeching)

488
00:34:33.249 --> 00:34:35.684
(rumbling)
(screeching)

489
00:34:46.461 --> 00:34:48.230
(roars)

490
00:34:50.266 --> 00:34:52.467
(Caraxes grumbling)

491
00:34:58.840 --> 00:35:00.543
All of you...

492
00:35:00.575 --> 00:35:02.812
sheathe the fucking steel.

493
00:35:08.783 --> 00:35:11.219
(distant dragon rumbling)

494
00:35:19.095 --> 00:35:21.263
(wings flapping)

495
00:35:24.300 --> 00:35:26.501
(Syrax screeching)

496
00:35:44.619 --> 00:35:46.388
(roars)

497
00:35:54.697 --> 00:35:56.898
(dragons screeching)

498
00:36:09.979 --> 00:36:12.781
- What are you doing here. Princess?
- Preventing bloodshed.

499
00:36:12.814 --> 00:36:15.917
Ser Criston. please escort
the Princess to safety.

500
00:36:15.950 --> 00:36:18.586
Take care not to startle Syrax.
my lords.

501
00:36:18.621 --> 00:36:20.755
She's rather protective of me.

502
00:36:22.349 --> 00:36:24.585
{\an8}(speaking High Valyrian)

503
00:37:07.802 --> 00:37:09.971
(waves crashing)

504
00:37:10.805 --> 00:37:13.142
I'm right here. Uncle...

505
00:37:15.009 --> 00:37:17.580
the object of your ire...

506
00:37:17.612 --> 00:37:20.548
the reason that you
were disinherited.

507
00:37:20.583 --> 00:37:22.984
If you wish to be
restored as heir.

508
00:37:23.017 --> 00:37:24.853
you'll need to kill me.

509
00:37:25.920 --> 00:37:27.288
So. do it.

510
00:37:28.256 --> 00:37:30.725
And be done
with all this bother.

511
00:37:57.720 --> 00:37:59.921
(footsteps departing)

512
00:38:12.101 --> 00:38:14.335
(intense music playing)

513
00:38:16.571 --> 00:38:18.374
(vocalizing)

514
00:38:28.049 --> 00:38:30.785
(Syrax screeches)

515
00:38:30.819 --> 00:38:33.621
(grumbles. roars)

516
00:38:34.956 --> 00:38:37.792
(triumphant music swells)

517
00:38:59.747 --> 00:39:01.916
(wind blowing)

518
00:39:11.125 --> 00:39:13.294
(metal clinking)

519
00:39:18.967 --> 00:39:21.170
(Prince Daemon sighs)

520
00:39:23.072 --> 00:39:26.442
Lady Mysaria: You announced that
we were to be wed?

521
00:39:27.343 --> 00:39:29.143
On the morrow.

522
00:39:30.546 --> 00:39:32.780
And that I was with child.

523
00:39:33.414 --> 00:39:34.849
Your child.

524
00:39:34.883 --> 00:39:38.253
Well. perhaps when we are wed.
we can make that true.

525
00:39:38.287 --> 00:39:40.456
I ensured long ago
that I would never be

526
00:39:40.488 --> 00:39:42.257
threatened by childbirth.

527
00:39:42.291 --> 00:39:45.260
Good. Children can be such
irritating creatures.

528
00:39:45.294 --> 00:39:48.197
You swore to protect me.
Daemon.

529
00:39:50.099 --> 00:39:52.534
Dragonstone is quite secure.

530
00:39:54.168 --> 00:39:58.741
Until the King decides to reclaim
his ancestral seat.

531
00:39:58.773 --> 00:40:01.609
His men might not put
the Prince's head on a spike.

532
00:40:01.643 --> 00:40:03.946
but what would they do
with the common whore

533
00:40:03.978 --> 00:40:06.814
he claims he's taken to wife
and made with child?

534
00:40:06.849 --> 00:40:08.683
No one will harm you.

535
00:40:09.585 --> 00:40:11.220
I have been sold as property

536
00:40:11.252 --> 00:40:13.856
more times than I care to count.

537
00:40:13.888 --> 00:40:18.560
beginning in a homeland
I can no longer recall.

538
00:40:18.594 --> 00:40:22.830
Most of my years have been spent
living in terror.

539
00:40:22.865 --> 00:40:24.967
You're safe with me. I swear it.

540
00:40:24.999 --> 00:40:26.434
You are Targaryen.

541
00:40:26.467 --> 00:40:28.169
You can afford to play

542
00:40:28.202 --> 00:40:29.704
your stupid games with the King.

543
00:40:29.737 --> 00:40:32.508
but I cannot.

544
00:40:32.540 --> 00:40:37.513
I didn't come into your service
wanting gold or power

545
00:40:37.545 --> 00:40:39.581
or station.

546
00:40:39.615 --> 00:40:43.751
- I came to you to be liberated.
- Liberated.

547
00:40:46.654 --> 00:40:48.056
From what?

548
00:40:49.158 --> 00:40:50.526
Fear.

549
00:40:52.093 --> 00:40:54.929
(pensive music playing)

550
00:41:15.950 --> 00:41:19.455
(door closes)
No. please. Lord Lyonel.

551
00:41:25.027 --> 00:41:27.895
I have come looking for
an unencumbered opinion.

552
00:41:27.930 --> 00:41:31.165
That's all I would
ever give. Your Grace.

553
00:41:31.599 --> 00:41:34.869
Ever since my name was read
by the archmaesters at the Great Council.

554
00:41:34.902 --> 00:41:38.474
I have felt Corlys Velaryon's
envious gaze staring at me

555
00:41:38.506 --> 00:41:40.843
from across the Blackwater.

556
00:41:40.875 --> 00:41:44.413
You sit upon the highest seat
in the realm. Your Grace.

557
00:41:44.445 --> 00:41:47.148
Proud men don't like
having to look up.

558
00:41:50.918 --> 00:41:53.121
Laena Velaryon.

559
00:41:54.188 --> 00:41:57.659
Lord Corlys is your
Master of Ships

560
00:41:57.693 --> 00:41:59.027
and she is the eldest daughter

561
00:41:59.061 --> 00:42:01.462
of the wealthiest
house in the realm.

562
00:42:01.497 --> 00:42:05.366
She comes from unimpeachable
Velaryon stock

563
00:42:05.400 --> 00:42:08.036
and she has Targaryen blood.

564
00:42:08.070 --> 00:42:11.105
- What's to mislike?
- She is 12.

565
00:42:11.139 --> 00:42:12.940
She will mature.

566
00:42:15.176 --> 00:42:17.346
I never asked to remarry.

567
00:42:17.378 --> 00:42:21.517
As King. you have a claim
on all things.

568
00:42:21.549 --> 00:42:22.684
Even those you don't want.

569
00:42:23.284 --> 00:42:26.054
Marriage is not an obligation
you can put off for long.

570
00:42:26.088 --> 00:42:28.790
What if I was to reject
Lord Corlys's proposal?

571
00:42:28.823 --> 00:42:31.627
He would not be like
to take it well.

572
00:42:31.659 --> 00:42:33.294
I fear nothing short
of a direct line

573
00:42:33.327 --> 00:42:36.230
to the Iron Throne
would satisfy him.

574
00:42:36.265 --> 00:42:39.067
You should also consider
that we find ourselves

575
00:42:39.101 --> 00:42:42.070
on the precipice of war
in the Stepstones.

576
00:42:42.471 --> 00:42:45.073
And the Sea Snake holds claim to nearly
half the realm's ships.

577
00:42:45.474 --> 00:42:49.645
He would not dare withhold them
in the face of the realm's need.

578
00:42:49.677 --> 00:42:53.382
- Who is he to hector me?
- No one. Your Grace.

579
00:42:54.615 --> 00:42:57.119
But Driftmark makes
for a better ally

580
00:42:57.151 --> 00:42:59.922
than it does an enemy.

581
00:42:59.954 --> 00:43:02.323
The Sea Snake has made
a calculated reach.

582
00:43:02.356 --> 00:43:04.859
a fair play for a man
of his position.

583
00:43:06.894 --> 00:43:11.767
- If you truly want my unencumbered opinion...
- I do.

584
00:43:11.799 --> 00:43:15.037
You should wed Laena Velaryon.
Your Grace.

585
00:43:15.069 --> 00:43:18.574
Sate Lord Corlys
and fix him at your side.

586
00:43:18.606 --> 00:43:21.909
permanently. as an ally.
(door opens)

587
00:43:25.246 --> 00:43:26.614
Ser Steffon Darklyn: Your Grace.

588
00:43:26.647 --> 00:43:29.851
the Princess has returned
from Dragonstone.

589
00:43:29.884 --> 00:43:31.652
Dragonstone?

590
00:43:31.687 --> 00:43:33.721
(tense music playing)

591
00:43:33.755 --> 00:43:36.058
(vocalizing)

592
00:43:51.540 --> 00:43:52.907
Your Grace.

593
00:43:56.577 --> 00:43:58.780
King Viserys: You disobeyed me.

594
00:43:58.814 --> 00:44:02.850
You fled King's Landing
without a word

595
00:44:02.884 --> 00:44:06.788
and you acted without
The Crown's leave.

596
00:44:09.690 --> 00:44:12.126
You are my only heir.

597
00:44:13.095 --> 00:44:15.296
You could've been killed.

598
00:44:18.699 --> 00:44:20.301
May I sit?

599
00:44:31.480 --> 00:44:33.749
You went to Dragonstone.

600
00:44:33.781 --> 00:44:36.218
And retrieved the egg
without bloodshed.

601
00:44:38.085 --> 00:44:41.657
A feat I'm not sure Ser Otto
could've accomplished alone.

602
00:44:44.559 --> 00:44:46.561
Yes. well...

603
00:44:46.595 --> 00:44:47.962
(chuckles)

604
00:44:51.133 --> 00:44:54.068
I sometimes forget
how alike you both were.

605
00:44:57.071 --> 00:44:58.439
(sighs)

606
00:45:04.146 --> 00:45:06.347
Your mother's absence

607
00:45:06.380 --> 00:45:08.617
is a wound that will never heal.

608
00:45:09.785 --> 00:45:11.752
Without her...

609
00:45:11.787 --> 00:45:13.387
the Red Keep has lost a warmth

610
00:45:13.422 --> 00:45:16.290
that I dare say
it will never recover.

611
00:45:16.324 --> 00:45:19.827
It pleases me
to hear you say this.

612
00:45:23.664 --> 00:45:27.069
To know that I'm not alone
in my grief.

613
00:45:27.101 --> 00:45:29.538
I wish I had known better

614
00:45:29.570 --> 00:45:32.139
what to say to you
in the aftermath.

615
00:45:34.475 --> 00:45:38.512
I struggled to realize that my daughter
had so quickly become a woman grown.

616
00:45:42.350 --> 00:45:44.418
But I know...

617
00:45:44.453 --> 00:45:48.222
she understands what
is now expected of me.

618
00:45:48.256 --> 00:45:50.992
The King must take a new wife.

619
00:45:55.796 --> 00:45:58.300
I could never
replace your mother.

620
00:46:00.202 --> 00:46:02.838
No more than I intend
to replace you as heir.

621
00:46:04.372 --> 00:46:06.475
But you are my only heir

622
00:46:06.507 --> 00:46:10.778
and our line is vulnerable.
too easily ended.

623
00:46:10.811 --> 00:46:12.948
And by marrying again.
I may begin to ensure

624
00:46:12.980 --> 00:46:15.783
- that we are better defended.
- Against whom?

625
00:46:15.816 --> 00:46:18.320
Whomever may dare
to challenge us.

626
00:46:24.659 --> 00:46:28.162
I do not wish
to make us estranged.

627
00:46:28.195 --> 00:46:30.097
You are the King...

628
00:46:30.132 --> 00:46:34.068
and so. your first duty
is to the realm.

629
00:46:36.837 --> 00:46:39.073
Mother would've understood this.

630
00:46:41.542 --> 00:46:43.345
Just as I do.

631
00:46:47.014 --> 00:46:48.416
(bell tolls)

632
00:46:48.449 --> 00:46:50.418
(birds cawing)

633
00:46:50.451 --> 00:46:53.287
(pensive music playing)

634
00:47:01.929 --> 00:47:03.732
(door opens)

635
00:47:06.535 --> 00:47:08.569
(indistinct chatter)

636
00:47:26.253 --> 00:47:28.055
(door closes)

637
00:47:29.991 --> 00:47:32.226
Good morrow. my lords.

638
00:47:43.104 --> 00:47:47.008
I have decided
to take a new wife.

639
00:48:05.159 --> 00:48:07.361
I intend to marry...

640
00:48:13.501 --> 00:48:15.936
the Lady Alicent Hightower

641
00:48:17.606 --> 00:48:19.808
before spring's end.

642
00:48:26.313 --> 00:48:28.182
This is an absurdity.

643
00:48:29.050 --> 00:48:31.887
My house is Valyrian.

644
00:48:31.919 --> 00:48:34.356
the greatest power in the realm.

645
00:48:35.457 --> 00:48:37.658
And I am your King.

646
00:48:44.665 --> 00:48:46.867
(tense music playing)

647
00:48:50.137 --> 00:48:51.907
(door opens)

648
00:48:54.708 --> 00:48:56.343
(door closes)

649
00:49:01.850 --> 00:49:03.717
King Viserys: Rhaenyra.

650
00:49:08.322 --> 00:49:09.690
(door opens)

651
00:49:25.706 --> 00:49:29.678
House Velaryon's origins
reach back to Old Valyria.

652
00:49:31.378 --> 00:49:34.281
More ancient even than
House Targaryen...

653
00:49:35.951 --> 00:49:38.185
according to some texts.

654
00:49:39.353 --> 00:49:42.022
But unlike the Targaryens.

655
00:49:42.057 --> 00:49:45.327
we were no dragonlords.

656
00:49:45.759 --> 00:49:49.965
For centuries. my house had to scratch out
an existence from the sea

657
00:49:49.997 --> 00:49:52.801
with grit and luck.

658
00:49:54.735 --> 00:49:57.439
When I ascended
the Driftwood Throne...

659
00:49:58.405 --> 00:50:00.241
I knew what I wanted.

660
00:50:02.009 --> 00:50:04.245
So I went out and seized it.

661
00:50:05.547 --> 00:50:06.947
Unlike every other
lord of the realm.

662
00:50:06.982 --> 00:50:10.085
I can say that I built
my house's high seat

663
00:50:10.117 --> 00:50:12.620
with the strength
of mine own back.

664
00:50:14.155 --> 00:50:16.390
(tense music playing)

665
00:50:18.859 --> 00:50:21.662
I've always thought of
you and I as having been

666
00:50:21.695 --> 00:50:23.764
made from the same cloth.

667
00:50:32.374 --> 00:50:35.309
I wasn't aware you had
a king for a brother.

668
00:50:35.342 --> 00:50:36.845
We're both men
who have had to cut

669
00:50:36.877 --> 00:50:39.680
our own way through the world.

670
00:50:39.713 --> 00:50:42.983
We've been passed over...
too often.

671
00:50:45.553 --> 00:50:46.596
Did you call me to Driftmark

672
00:50:47.022 --> 00:50:49.256
to remind me of my
low standing. Lord Corlys.

673
00:50:49.290 --> 00:50:51.525
or was there some other reason?

674
00:50:54.963 --> 00:50:57.599
You've heard of the troubles
in the Stepstones?

675
00:50:59.300 --> 00:51:01.236
Daemon: Some Myrish Prince

676
00:51:01.268 --> 00:51:04.338
is feeding Westerosi
sailors to the crabs.

677
00:51:04.705 --> 00:51:07.274
Corlys: I have been petitioning
the King to send my navy

678
00:51:07.308 --> 00:51:09.109
into the territory.

679
00:51:09.144 --> 00:51:10.911
but he's denied me.

680
00:51:10.945 --> 00:51:14.949
- It was never my brother's strongest trait.
- What?

681
00:51:16.151 --> 00:51:17.818
Being King.

682
00:51:21.890 --> 00:51:24.259
Corlys: The Crabfeeder is backed
by powerful entities

683
00:51:24.658 --> 00:51:29.164
within the Free Cities who wish to see
Westeros weakened.

684
00:51:29.196 --> 00:51:31.031
(sailor grunting)
And the King's failures

685
00:51:31.066 --> 00:51:34.169
have allowed him
to accumulate strength.

686
00:51:35.637 --> 00:51:38.672
If those shipping lanes fall.

687
00:51:38.706 --> 00:51:41.375
my house will be crippled.

688
00:51:41.408 --> 00:51:43.744
And I will not have Driftmark
beggared while our King

689
00:51:43.777 --> 00:51:47.381
idles himself with feasts
and balls and tourneys.

690
00:51:47.414 --> 00:51:50.718
I will speak of
my brother as I wish.

691
00:51:52.419 --> 00:51:54.089
You will not.

692
00:51:57.292 --> 00:51:59.059
Waiting in the Stepstones

693
00:51:59.094 --> 00:52:01.328
is a chance for you
to prove your worth

694
00:52:01.362 --> 00:52:03.998
to any who might yet doubt it.

695
00:52:05.332 --> 00:52:08.235
We are the realm's
second sons. Daemon.

696
00:52:09.503 --> 00:52:11.705
Our worth is not given.

697
00:52:13.073 --> 00:52:15.242
It must be made.

698
00:52:36.064 --> 00:52:38.358
(intense music playing)

698
00:52:39.305 --> 00:53:39.453
